    "design_priorities": "# V2.6 Lead Architect Design Priorities\n\n## Current priorities (in order)\n\n### P1: Production operational hardening (before expansion)\n- Add retry/backoff to gemini_client.py\n- Add explicit timeout configuration\n- Add provider-level fallback chain (Gemini \u2192 OpenAI)\n- Add rate limit awareness / queueing\n- Priority: **high** \u2014 required before broader rollout\n\n### P2: ru_econ_10 investigation (bounded)\n- Diagnose why SC-6 (register preservation) always fails for this case\n- Determine if it is recoverable with bounded prompt refinement\n- If not recoverable: accept as permanent known limitation\n- Priority: **medium** \u2014 does not block expansion, but affects RU acceptance rate\n\n### P3: Monitoring / observability\n- Add structured logging for fallback triggers\n- Add latency histograms per provider\n- Add guardian decision counters (accept/revert by reason)\n- Add rate limit proximity alerting\n- Priority: **medium** \u2014 required for production confidence\n\n### P4: Broader case coverage\n- Expand eval set beyond 5 high-AI cases\n- Include more diverse RU and EN domains\n- Validate that 80% acceptance holds on larger case set\n- Priority: **medium** \u2014 required before full production\n\n## What is explicitly NOT a priority\n- Architecture expansion (locked at 4-role)\n- Harmonizer introduction (excluded)\n- New role addition (excluded)\n- Mid-AI processing (secondary, not primary target)\n- Provider search (Gemini validated as primary)\n- Detector optimization (not in scope)\n\n## Design constraints\n- All changes must stay inside the `4-role + Gemini` frame\n- Guardian policy cannot be loosened without measured justification\n- Prompt changes allowed only if bounded and measurable\n- No changes that require BDC re-evaluation of the architecture frame\n",
